POINTS:
- [tycho-extras/tycho-pomless/src/main/java/org/eclipse/tycho/pomless/TychoFeatureMapping.java:46] The problem is the ".xml" extension.
When `PolyglotModelManager.getReaderFor()` is called it asks each mapping (in descending priority order) if it accepts the given options. And `MappingSupport.accept()` falsely returns true for a `feature.xml`:
```
  public boolean accept(final Map<String, ?> options) {
    if (options != null) {
      for (String key : getAcceptOptionKeys()) {
        if (options.containsKey(key)) {
          return true;
        }
      }
      String location = getLocation(options);
      if (location != null) {
        for (String ext : getAcceptLocationExtensions()) {
          if (location.endsWith(ext)) {
            return true;
          }
        }
      }
    }
    return false;
  }
```
The XML-model in the feature.xml file (usually) does not have the "xml:4.0.0" options-key set, but its location ends with `feature.xml`. In fact that Mapping accepts itself to provide a reader for any XML-file. That's the issue.
Until now we are (probably) lucky that the `XMLMapping` is always sorted behind the `TychoFeatureMapping` in `PolyglotModelManager.getSortedMappings()`, but I assume that this is an implementation detail of plexus.

